args.file_text:
import time
import hashlib
import bcrypt
import csv

# Test users data
test_users = [
    {"username": "user1", "raw_password": "password123"},
    {"username": "user2", "raw_password": "securePass!"},
    {"username": "admin", "raw_password": "Admin@1234"}
]

def benchmark_hashing():
    results = []
    
    for user in test_users:
        # SHA-256 benchmark
        start = time.time()
        sha_hash = hashlib.sha256(user["raw_password"].encode()).hexdigest()
        sha_time = time.time() - start
        
        # bcrypt benchmark
        start = time.time()
        bcrypt_hash = bcrypt.hashpw(user["raw_password"].encode(), bcrypt.gensalt())
        bcrypt_time = time.time() - start
        
        results.append({
            "username": user["username"],
            "sha256_time": sha_time,
            "bcrypt_time": bcrypt_time
        })
    
    # Save results to CSV
    with open("/workspace/benchmark_results.csv", "w") as f:
        writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=["username", "sha256_time", "bcrypt_time"])
        writer.writeheader()
        writer.writerows(results)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    benchmark_hashing()
